  "Schema": 1,
  "Description": "Build s&box games by talking to Claude. 150+ tools to drive the s&box editor through conversation — GameObjects, scripts, scenes, components, physics, networking, UI, world-gen, lighting & atmosphere, characters, scene layout, navmesh & spatial queries, particles, scatter & object utilities, type discovery. v1.5.0 adds 16 tools (self-diagnosis read_log/get_compile_errors, aimed screenshot_from, bake_navmesh/get_navmesh_path, physics_overlap, bake_reflections, spawn_vpcf, console_run/execute_csharp, search_docs) plus a security & correctness hardening pass (handler errors now report success=false, path-traversal safety on all file handlers, atomic IPC). If you use Claude Code, install the companion plugin: `/plugin marketplace add LouSputthole/Sbox-Claude` then `/plugin install sbox-claude` — it bundles the MCP server registration plus an `sbox-build-feature` skill that codifies the screenshot-driven iteration workflow. See TROUBLESHOOTING.md if anything misbehaves.",
